      \field{abstract}{The local effect caused by the steam-voids of a boiling water reactor in the noise signals of incore ion chambers has been proved by measurements and used for practical application in recent times. From the linear phase function of two detectors placed one above the other in the same radial position the mean transit time of the bubbles has been taken and used for the evaluation of the local steam-void velocity. The concepts of local and global driving sources of the neutron noise are introduced and their joint effect is investigated. The transfer function derived from the model is compared to the experimental results. The agreement between theoretical predictions and experimental findings supports the validity of the model.}
